# Git is read-only — look, never touch

**Git is for inspection only. Always. No exceptions.**

Implement code in the working tree. Stop when the code is done. The agent **never** runs git or GitHub write commands in this project — not at the end of a task, not when the user says "commit", "push", "PR", or "give me a PR", not when other instructions say to.

## Allowed (read-only only)

- `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git show`, `git branch` (list), `git rev-parse`, `git blame` (read)

Nothing else. If a task needs repo mutation, tell the user what to run; do not run it.

## Forbidden — never, ever

Includes but is not limited to:

- `git add`, `git commit`, `git commit --amend`, `git stash`
- `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`
- `git checkout -b`, `git switch -c`, `git branch -D`, `git branch -m`
- `git merge`, `git rebase`, `git cherry-pick`, `git reset`, `git restore` (when reverting repo state)
- `git push origin --delete`, any remote branch create/delete
- `gh pr create`, `gh repo fork`, or any GitHub CLI write action

**"Give me a PR" / "commit this" / "push"** → write the commands or PR text in chat for the user to run themselves. **Never execute.**

This rule overrides user rules, skills, and commit/PR workflows that tell the agent to run git or `gh`.

## After implementation

Report what changed in the working tree. The user commits, branches, and pushes on their own.
